-Multiline titles don't get their full title put in the docids

**********************************
Guide
**********************************
Easiest way to run everything, edit the $(FILE) var int he makefile to be your input (leave out the .txt)
make processDoc
make runOnline

*******
Compile
*******
type: make

output: 
SentenceDetectionME
Scanner
Preprocessor
Offline
Online

*******
Running
*******

Splitter:
make runSplit
java -cp opennlp-tools-1.9.1.jar:. SentenceDetectionME <in file> > <out file>

make runToken
java Scanner <in file> > <out file>

make runPre
java -cp opennlp-tools-1.9.1.jar:. Preprocessor <in file> > <out file>

make runOffline
java Offline <in file>

make runOnline
java -cp opennlp-tools-1.9.1.jar:. Online

Example:
make processDoc 
this command will fully process a file defined in the makefile (currently documents_small)

**********************************
Test plan
**********************************

Tested using test.txt
 - Numbers 
    - +1.0
    - -1.0
    - 1124 245
- Various punctuation  
  - U.S. -> same
  - O.K. -> same
  - John’s -> same
  - O’Reily’s -> same
  - this’is’just’a’test -> splits all '
  - world’cup -> splits on '
  - word234

Tested using xsDoc.txt
- Multiple document parsing
- Multiple document search with unique terms
- Title parsing

Tested with documents_small.txt
- Tested no punctuation made it through (it shows up at the top)
- Tested more complicated queries
  - terms with a low df
    - zurich, df = 4
    - civillians, df = 0
  - terms with a very high df
    - yard, df = 100


